                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 761.94/93</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Francis</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-18T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1916, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>790. The Embassy at Tokyo recently reported publication in Japan of terms of an
                    alliance between Russia and Japan. Although Foreign Office denied report the
                    Embassy believed such a treaty about to be signed. Discreetly ascertain the
                    facts if possible. Telegraph outline terms agreed upon or proposed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
